text.section:
The Department of Juvenile Justice shall promulgate and enforce administrative regulations to govern at least the following aspects of the operation of facilities:
Administration;
Personnel;
Training and staff development;
Recordkeeping;
Physical plant;
Security and control;
Safety and emergency procedures;
Sanitation and hygiene;
Medical and health services;
Food services;
Intake and classification;
Programs and services;
Residents' rights;
Rules and discipline;
Admission procedures;
Communication, including mail, visitation, and telephone;
Release preparation and transfer programs;
Volunteer involvement;
Transfers;
Reimbursement rates and conditions; and
Detention facility rate increases.
